At least 45 people were killed when residents of Kwa-Madala hostel near Vanderbijlpark, attacked community members on the 17th of June, 1992.(SABC)Saturday marks the 25th commemoration of the Boipatong massacre. At least 45 people were killed when residents of Kwa-Madala hostel near Vanderbijlpark, attacked community members on June 17, 1992. Speaking &#160;in Boipatong where the party held its youth day rally, EFF leader Julius Malema said the community has a very important place in the history of South Africa. For more watch videos below: